newsletters.name: Hannah Arendt on Love and How to Live with the Fundamental Fear of Loss
newsletters.description: “Love, but be careful what you love,” the Roman African philosopher Saint Augustine wrote in the final years of the fourth century. We are, in some deep sense, what we love — we become it as much as it becomes us, beckoned from our myriad conscious and unconscious longings, despairs, and patterned desires.
